---
import DefaultLayout from "../../layouts/default.astro";
---

<DefaultLayout title="Naviget Privacy Policy">
    <div
        class="border-default p-6 mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl tracking-wider justify-around md:p-12"
    >
        <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl tracking-tight text-heading md:text-6xl">
            Naviget Privacy policy
        </h1>

        <p class="font-normal text-body mb-3">Effective Date: 5 May 2025</p>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            StepZero Labs Private Limited (“we,” “our,” or “us”) operates the
            Naviget app and website https://naviget.in (the “Service”). This
            Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose your
            personal information when you use our Service.
        </p>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            By using Naviget, you agree to the collection and use of information
            in accordance with this policy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">
            1. Information We Collect
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-heading text-xl mb-2 mt-4">
            a. Information You Provide
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                Account Information: Name, email address, phone number, and
                password.
            </li>

            <li>
                Profile Details: Profile photo, payment preferences, language
                preferences.
            </li>

            <li>
                Booking Information: Pickup and drop locations, ride history.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-heading text-xl mb-2 mt-4">
            b. Information We Collect Automatically
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                Location Data: Real-time GPS location (only when the app is in
                use or background, with your permission).
            </li>

            <li>
                Device Information: Device type, OS version, IP address, browser
                type, crash reports.
            </li>

            <li>
                Usage Data: App interaction, features used, time spent, and
                referring URLs.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-heading text-xl mb-2 mt-4">
            c. Information from Third Parties
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>Payment Processors: To confirm payment success/failure.</li>
            <li>Marketing Partners: For analytics and campaign tracking.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">
            2. How We Use Your Information
        </h2>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>To facilitate ride bookings and track your rides.</li>
            <li>
                To improve the performance, safety, and user experience of our
                app.
            </li>
            <li>
                To send transactional alerts, booking updates, and support
                messages.
            </li>
            <li>To process payments and provide invoices.</li>
            <li>To detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and security incidents.</li>
            <li>For analytics, product research, and development.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">
            3. Sharing Your Information
        </h2>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            We do not sell your personal information. However, we may share it
            in the following circumstances:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                <b>Drivers/Service Partners:</b> To fulfill your ride or delivery
                request.
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Vendors & Service Providers:</b> For hosting, analytics, customer
                support, or marketing services.
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Legal Compliance:</b> When required by law or to protect our legal
                rights.
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Business Transfers:</b> In the case of a merger, sale, or asset
                transfer.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">4. Your Choices</h2>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                You may update your account info at any time in the app
                settings.
            </li>
            <li>
                You can disable location sharing via your device settings (this
                may impact ride functionality).
            </li>
            <li>
                You may opt out of promotional emails or push notifications
                in-app or via email footer links.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">5. Data Retention</h2>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            We retain your personal information for as long as your account is
            active or as needed to provide services. We may also retain
            information as required by law or for legitimate business purposes
            (e.g., to prevent fraud or enforce our terms).
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">6. Security</h2>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            We implement industry-standard measures such as HTTPS, encryption at
            rest, and secure storage to protect your data. However, no method of
            transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">7. Children’s Privacy</h2>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            Our Service is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do
            not knowingly collect information from minors.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">
            8. International Transfers
        </h2>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            If you access Naviget outside India, your information may be
            transferred to and processed in India or other countries where our
            infrastructure is located.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">
            9. Changes to This Policy
        </h2>
        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We’ll notify
            you of major changes via in-app notifications or email. The latest
            version will always be available at
            <a href="https://naviget.in">https://naviget.in</a>
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">10. Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:
            StepZero Labs Private Limited, Pavani Sreshta, Silver Spring Layout,
            Munnekollal, EPIP, Bangalore Email:
            <a href="mailto:hello@naviget.in">hello@naviget.in</a>
            Website:<a href="https://naviget.in"> https://naviget.in</a>
        </p>
    </div>
</DefaultLayout>
